{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Organization",
  "name": "[Organization Full Name]",
  "alternateName": "[Alternate Name or Abbreviation]",
  "url": "https://yourdomain.com",
  "logo": {
    "@type": "ImageObject",
    "url": "https://yourdomain.com/logo.png",
    "width": 600,
    "height": 60
  },
  "image": "https://yourdomain.com/images/organization-photo.jpg",
  "description": "[1-2 sentence description of what the organization does]",
  "foundingDate": "2018-01-15",
  "founders": [
    {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "[Founder Full Name]",
      "url": "https://yourdomain.com/about/founder"
    }
  ],
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "streetAddress": "[123 Main Street, Suite 100]",
    "addressLocality": "[City]",
    "addressRegion": "[State/Province]",
    "postalCode": "[ZIP/Postal Code]",
    "addressCountry": "[US]"
  },
  "contactPoint": [
    {
      "@type": "ContactPoint",
      "telephone": "[+1-555-123-4567]",
      "contactType": "Customer Service",
      "email": "contact@yourdomain.com",
      "availableLanguage": ["English"],
      "areaServed": ["US", "CA"]
    },
    {
      "@type": "ContactPoint",
      "telephone": "[+1-555-123-4568]",
      "contactType": "Sales",
      "email": "sales@yourdomain.com"
    }
  ],
  "sameAs": [
    "https://twitter.com/yourorg",
    "https://linkedin.com/company/yourorg",
    "https://facebook.com/yourorg",
    "https://instagram.com/yourorg",
    "https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q12345678"
  ],
  "aggregateRating": {
    "@type": "AggregateRating",
    "ratingValue": "4.8",
    "reviewCount": "127",
    "bestRating": "5",
    "worstRating": "1"
  },
  "numberOfEmployees": {
    "@type": "QuantitativeValue",
    "value": 50
  },
  "location": {
    "@type": "Place",
    "name": "[Office Name]",
    "address": {
      "@type": "PostalAddress",
      "streetAddress": "[123 Main Street]",
      "addressLocality": "[City]",
      "addressRegion": "[State]",
      "postalCode": "[ZIP]",
      "addressCountry": "[US]"
    }
  }
}

/*
SPECIALIZED ORGANIZATION TYPES:

For more specific schema types, replace "@type": "Organization" with:

1. LocalBusiness (Physical Location):
   "@type": "LocalBusiness"
   - Add: "openingHours", "geo", "priceRange"
   - Use for: Retail stores, restaurants, offices

2. MedicalBusiness (Healthcare):
   "@type": "MedicalBusiness"
   - Add: "medicalSpecialty", "availableService"
   - Use for: Clinics, hospitals, medical practices

3. ProfessionalService:
   "@type": "ProfessionalService"
   - Add: "priceRange", "areaServed", "serviceType"
   - Use for: Consulting, legal, accounting firms

4. EducationalOrganization:
   "@type": "EducationalOrganization"
   - Add: "alumni", "department"
   - Use for: Schools, universities, training centers

5. Corporation:
   "@type": "Corporation"
   - Add: "tickerSymbol", "numberOfEmployees"
   - Use for: Public companies

USAGE NOTES:

1. Organization Identity:
   - Use consistent name across web
   - Include common alternate names
   - Match Google Business Profile exactly
   - No variations or abbreviations

2. NAP Consistency (Critical for Local):
   - Name, Address, Phone must match EXACTLY
   - Use same format everywhere
   - Include complete address with ZIP
   - Use E.164 format for phone (+1-555-123-4567)

3. Logo Requirements:
   - Square or rectangular
   - Minimum 112Ã—112px
   - Maximum 10MB
   - PNG, JPG, or WebP
   - Transparent background preferred

4. sameAs (Authority Signals):
   - Link to official social profiles
   - Include Wikipedia/Wikidata if available
   - Google Scholar for research orgs
   - Crunchbase for companies
   - Must be verified/official accounts

5. Contact Information:
   - Multiple contact types (Sales, Support, etc.)
   - Include email and phone
   - Specify languages supported
   - Define service areas

KNOWLEDGE GRAPH OPTIMIZATION:

Google Knowledge Panel Requirements:
1. Consistent NAP across 10+ citations
2. Claimed Google Business Profile
3. Active social media profiles
4. Official website with Organization schema
5. Media mentions and press coverage
6. Wikidata entry (if eligible)

Entity Recognition Signals:
- Official website with org schema
- Social media profiles linked (sameAs)
- Consistent information across web
- Reviews and ratings
- Press coverage
- Industry recognition

EXAMPLES:

Medical Clinic:
{
  "@type": "MedicalBusiness",
  "name": "199 Clinic",
  "medicalSpecialty": "Aesthetic Medicine, Regenerative Therapy",
  "description": "Board-certified physicians providing aesthetic medicine and personalized wellness plans.",
  "priceRange": "$$$",
  "sameAs": [
    "https://linkedin.com/company/199clinic",
    "https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q12345678"
  ]
}

Consulting Firm:
{
  "@type": "ProfessionalService",
  "name": "Strategic Advisory Group",
  "serviceType": "Management Consulting, Strategy",
  "areaServed": {
    "@type": "Country",
    "name": "United States"
  }
}

Tech Company:
{
  "@type": "Corporation",
  "name": "TechCorp Inc.",
  "tickerSymbol": "TECH",
  "numberOfEmployees": 250,
  "foundingDate": "2015"
}

AI PLATFORM BENEFITS:

